notesStmt.note: Several owner's stamps (f. 1r, 2r); one with the name Muḥammad Ḥusayn...Shāh dated 1070? AH (1659-1660 CE) and one dated 1063 AH (1652-1653 CE) on which the name is illegible (f. 1r).

msContents.summary: A history of the Muzaffarid dynasty until 767 AH; the first page is a replacement in a different hand.
msContents.textLang: Persian with some phrases in Arabic

respStmt.persName: Maḥmūd ibn Muḥammad ibn Maḥmūd, active 1431

supportDesc.extent: i, 208, i leaves : 248 x 170 (171 x 105) mm, bound to 248 x 170 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written chiefly in naskh with one page in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Dual-page illuminated opening in three registers in blue (two diffrent shades) and gold (f. 1v-2r); textblock border-ruled in gold; rubrications in red.

binding.p: Red leather over pasteboard with brown paper onlay central mandorla and two pendants on the vertical axis; marbled paper pastedowns.

origin.p: Copy completed in Jumādá al-Thānī 834 AH (February 1431 CE) by Maḥmūd ibn Muḥammad ibn Maḥmūd (f. 208r).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Muḥammad Ṣadr al-Dīn in 1225 A.H. (1810 CE) (stamp, f. 1r).
